# Gravitris has no server and no runtime configuration — it is a single
# offline Android game with no accounts, no network permission, and no
# environment-dependent behaviour on the device. There is nothing here for
# the *app* to read.
#
# The variables below configure the *build*, not the product. Copy this file
# to .env and source it (`set -a; source .env; set +a`), or export them
# directly — either way, `make setup`/`make test`/`make build`/`make dev` will
# pick them up.

# Where the Android SDK (platform, build-tools, platform-tools) lives.
# `make setup` installs the pinned SDK components here if the directory
# doesn't already have them; Gradle/AGP reads this instead of a committed
# local.properties (which is machine-specific and gitignored on purpose).
# Default matches the Makefile's default — override only if you already
# manage an SDK install elsewhere.
ANDROID_HOME=/state/android-sdk

# Uncomment to point Gradle's dependency/build cache somewhere other than the
# default ($HOME/.gradle). Not needed in the team container — $HOME is
# already /state, so caches land there without help.
# GRADLE_USER_HOME=/state/.gradle
